# The intake grammar for the Loudon lion corpus (bench/loudon_lion_corpus.py) -- 50 verbatim
# sentences of Mrs. Loudon's *Entertaining Naturalist*, translated to CNL by an LLM with every
# sentence recorded (nothing silently dropped).
#
# Design: docs/design/homoiconic_grammar.md. This file is the honest test of the arc: the lion
# grammar in corpus/lion_grammar.cnl was written against 7 sentences chosen to exercise gaps we
# already knew about. This one is written against a corpus nobody wrote for us.
#
# PROTOCOL: written in ONE pass from the corpus VOCABULARY plus ordinary English constructions,
# before running it. Whatever it fails to cover is a real finding, not a grammar bug to quietly
# patch. bench/spike_loudon_grammar.py records the first-pass number.
#
# Beyond corpus/lion_grammar.cnl this adds: predicative adjectives (`the lion is strong`),
# copula-with-noun-phrase subsumption (`the lion is a cat`), and a second preposition (`at`).

# HEDGING (2026-07-20, the concept-inventory audit's most frequent gap -- sentences 8/12/13/18/24/37).
# A hedged clause is its OWN category (`hclause`), which is what keeps `clause asserts ...` from
# firing on it: a hedged sentence must NOT write an ink fact. `clause expands to hclause` only makes
# it reachable from the root and deliberately percolates NO slots. The band the hedge word denotes
# is NOT declared here -- it is the KB-level hedge lexicon (`uncertainty.hedge_bands`, `X means N`),
# the same scale the possibilistic layer already reads.

# ---- lexicon: closed classes ----
the is a determiner
a is a determiner
no is a negator
is is a copula
than is a comparator
in is a preposition
at is a preposition
generally is a hedge
usually is a hedge
sometimes is a hedge
occasionally is a hedge

# ...and the band each one denotes. Same surface as the KB hedge lexicon (`X means N`), and it must
# be declared HERE because the fold needs it as a compile-time constant (one rule per hedge word).
generally means 0.75
usually means 0.75
sometimes means 0.4
occasionally means 0.25

# ---- lexicon: content words ----
african is a modifier
asiatic is a modifier
bengal is a modifier
persian is a modifier
guzerat is a modifier
lion is a noun
cat is a noun
mane is a noun
tail is a noun
africa is a noun
asia is a noun
jungles is a noun
night is a noun
strong is a adj
smaller is a comparative
has is a transitive
roars is a intransitive
lives is a intransitive
hunts is a intransitive

# ---- productions ----
np expands to noun
np expands to determiner plus np
np expands to modifier plus np
np expands to negator plus np
np expands to np plus pp
pp expands to preposition plus np
vp expands to intransitive
vp expands to transitive plus np
vp expands to vp plus pp
vp expands to copula plus adj
vp expands to copula plus np
vp expands to copula plus ap
cp expands to comparator plus np
ap expands to comparative plus cp
clause expands to np plus vp
hvp expands to hedge plus vp
hclause expands to np plus hvp
clause expands to hclause

# ---- how each slot is filled ----
slot head in np from noun is only head
slot head in np from determiner plus np is right head
slot head in np from modifier plus np is right head
slot attr in np from modifier plus np is left head
slot head in np from negator plus np is right head
slot neg in np from negator plus np is left head
slot head in np from np plus pp is left head
slot prep in np from np plus pp is right prep
slot pobj in np from np plus pp is right pobj
slot prep in pp from preposition plus np is left head
slot pobj in pp from preposition plus np is right head
slot pred in vp from intransitive is only head
slot pred in vp from transitive plus np is left head
slot obj in vp from transitive plus np is right head
slot neg in vp from transitive plus np is right neg
slot pred in vp from vp plus pp is left pred
slot obj in vp from vp plus pp is left obj
slot prep in vp from vp plus pp is right prep
slot pobj in vp from vp plus pp is right pobj
slot adjc in vp from copula plus adj is right head
slot kind in vp from copula plus np is right head
slot cobj in cp from comparator plus np is right head
slot comp in ap from comparative plus cp is left head
slot cobj in ap from comparative plus cp is right cobj
slot comp in vp from copula plus ap is right comp
slot cobj in vp from copula plus ap is right cobj
slot subj in clause from np plus vp is left head
slot pred in clause from np plus vp is right pred
slot obj in clause from np plus vp is right obj
slot neg in clause from np plus vp is right neg
slot prep in clause from np plus vp is right prep
slot pobj in clause from np plus vp is right pobj
slot comp in clause from np plus vp is right comp
slot cobj in clause from np plus vp is right cobj
slot adjc in clause from np plus vp is right adjc
slot kind in clause from np plus vp is right kind

# the hedge itself, plus the ordinary clause slots carried through the hedged shape
slot hedge in hvp from hedge plus vp is left head
slot pred in hvp from hedge plus vp is right pred
slot obj in hvp from hedge plus vp is right obj
slot adjc in hvp from hedge plus vp is right adjc
slot kind in hvp from hedge plus vp is right kind
slot neg in hvp from hedge plus vp is right neg
slot prep in hvp from hedge plus vp is right prep
slot pobj in hvp from hedge plus vp is right pobj
slot comp in hvp from hedge plus vp is right comp
slot cobj in hvp from hedge plus vp is right cobj
slot subj in hclause from np plus hvp is left head
slot hedge in hclause from np plus hvp is right hedge
slot pred in hclause from np plus hvp is right pred
slot obj in hclause from np plus hvp is right obj
slot adjc in hclause from np plus hvp is right adjc
slot kind in hclause from np plus hvp is right kind
slot neg in hclause from np plus hvp is right neg
slot prep in hclause from np plus hvp is right prep
slot pobj in hclause from np plus hvp is right pobj
slot comp in hclause from np plus hvp is right comp
slot cobj in hclause from np plus hvp is right cobj

# ---- which slots become facts ----
# `hedges` is the possibilistic verb: the triple goes in PENCIL behind a fork banded by the hedge
# word, so a hedged sentence commits NO ink. `hclause` being its own category is what keeps the
# plain `clause asserts ...` lines from firing on it as well.
np asserts head is attr
clause asserts subj pred obj unless neg
clause denies subj pred obj when neg
clause asserts subj pred true unless obj
clause asserts subj prep pobj when pobj
clause asserts subj comp cobj when cobj
clause asserts subj is adjc when adjc
# ---- KIND vs PROPERTY is decided by the DETERMINER (2026-07-20) ----
# `the lion is a cat` is a KIND assertion; `bo is cleared` is a PROPERTY. English marks the
# difference with the determiner and the surface carries it -- the grammar used to throw it away,
# because `copula plus np` fires whether or not a determiner is present. With an OPEN vocabulary
# (an undeclared word defaults to `noun`) that made every predicative adjective a kind: measured,
# `bo is cleared` committed `bo is_a cleared` where the shipped route commits `bo is cleared`.
# Parsed, routed `fact`, wrong predicate, no complaint -- form_inventory 8's "misunderstanding is a
# MIS-MAPPING". Guarding on the `det` slot needs NO new category.
# The subject's own determiner cannot interfere: a clause takes `det` from its RIGHT child (the vp).
clause asserts subj is_a kind when det
clause asserts subj is kind unless det
# The hedged counterparts. `hedges under hedge` says WHICH slot carries the band, once, so each
# line's own `when`/`unless` guard is free -- which is what lets the intransitive and prepositional
# shapes exist at all. These mirror the `clause asserts ...` lines above ONE FOR ONE: a hedged
# sentence must be able to say everything a plain one can, or the gap is silent (the sentence
# parses, routes as `fact`, and commits nothing).
hclause hedges under hedge
hclause hedges subj pred obj unless neg
hclause hedges subj pred true unless obj
hclause hedges subj prep pobj when pobj
hclause hedges subj comp cobj when cobj
hclause hedges subj is adjc when adjc
hclause hedges subj is_a kind when kind

# ---- FORCE: questions (2026-07-20, design/form_inventory.md 4b) ----
# `asks` is the third force verb beside `asserts`/`denies`/`hedges`, and the one that commits
# NOTHING: it generates no fold rule at all. The declaration says only WHICH SLOTS carry the asked
# triple; `grammar_intake.question_of` reads them and the router answers. A question is not a weaker
# assertion -- answering it changes no beliefs -- which is why it is a difference in FORCE, not in
# content, and why `qclause` must be its own category (so `clause asserts ...` cannot fire on it).
whether is a qmark

qbody expands to np plus adj
qbody expands to np plus np
qbody expands to np plus vp
qclause expands to copula plus qbody
qclause expands to copula plus np
qclause expands to qmark plus clause
clause expands to qclause

slot subj in qbody from np plus adj is left head
slot adjc in qbody from np plus adj is right head
slot subj in qbody from np plus np is left head
slot kind in qbody from np plus np is right head
slot subj in qbody from np plus vp is left head
slot pred in qbody from np plus vp is right pred
slot obj in qbody from np plus vp is right obj
slot adjc in qbody from np plus vp is right adjc

slot subj in qclause from copula plus qbody is right subj
slot adjc in qclause from copula plus qbody is right adjc
slot kind in qclause from copula plus qbody is right kind
slot pred in qclause from copula plus qbody is right pred
slot obj in qclause from copula plus qbody is right obj

qclause asks subj pred obj when obj
qclause asks subj is adjc when adjc
# THE QUESTION SIDE MUST AGREE WITH THE ASSERTION SIDE, and this half is the one that matters most:
# it was 25 of the 44 failures when the step-2 flip was simulated. Patching only `clause` fixed
# ZERO, because `is ada watched` still ASKED `('ada','is_a','watched')` while the rule had derived
# `('ada','is','watched')` -- so every derived PROPERTY answered `no (assumed)`. A question and an
# assertion that disagree about the predicate are a silent mismatch in both directions.
qclause asks subj is_a kind when det
qclause asks subj is kind unless det

# `whether P` embeds a real `clause`, so `clause asserts ...` would fire on it and the QUESTION would
# assert its own content (measured: `whether lion is huge` wrote `lion is_a huge`). That is the force
# failure form_inventory 8 describes -- perfect content mapping, zero force. The domination gate built
# for conditionals is exactly the mechanism, so questions reuse it rather than adding a second one.
qclause suppresses

slot subj in qclause from qmark plus clause is right subj
slot adjc in qclause from qmark plus clause is right adjc
slot kind in qclause from qmark plus clause is right kind
slot pred in qclause from qmark plus clause is right pred
slot obj in qclause from qmark plus clause is right obj

# ---- FORCE: goals (2026-07-20) ----
# `intends` is the force that commits no FACT but LEAVES SOMETHING BEHIND -- a `<goal>` node the act
# loop runs on. Like `qclause`, `gclause` suppresses its complement: `goal lion is a target` must not
# ASSERT that the lion is a target, it must ask for it to become one.
goal is a goalmark
gclause expands to goalmark plus clause
clause expands to gclause
gclause suppresses

slot subj in gclause from goalmark plus clause is right subj
slot kind in gclause from goalmark plus clause is right kind

gclause intends subj is_a kind when kind

# ---- the DETERMINER slot, percolated to every category that carries a `kind` ----
# `det` is present ONLY when an np was built from `determiner plus np`, so its PRESENCE is the
# discriminator the `when det` / `unless det` guards above read. It must reach every path a `kind`
# slot reaches, or the guard silently falls to the `unless` branch and a kind becomes a property.
slot det in np from determiner plus np is left head
slot det in vp from copula plus np is right det
slot det in clause from np plus vp is right det
slot det in hvp from hedge plus vp is right det
slot det in hclause from np plus hvp is right det
# the question side
slot det in qbody from np plus np is right det
slot det in qbody from np plus vp is right det
slot det in qclause from copula plus qbody is right det
slot det in qclause from copula plus np is right det
slot det in qclause from qmark plus clause is right det

# ---- FORCE: commands (2026-07-20, design/form_inventory.md 4b) ----
# The SPEECH ACTS -- `focus on lion`, `be cautious`, `run build`. Like `asks` and `intends` these
# commit no fact; unlike either, what they leave behind is a change of STEPPING state (a focus
# frame, the policy register, a `<run>` request) rather than anything the KB believes.
#
# WHY THIS COMPOSES WITHOUT AMBIGUITY, and it is structural rather than lucky: English marks force
# POSITIONALLY, at the LEFT EDGE. An imperative in initial position cannot collide with a fact,
# because every fact production starts with an np and there is no `np plus np` to give the noun
# reading anywhere to go. Measured, not assumed -- declaring these words as nouns TOO still parses
# every surface unambiguously.
#
# `iclause` needs no `suppresses`. `qclause`/`gclause` suppress because they embed a whole `clause`
# that `clause asserts ...` would fire on; an iclause embeds only an np/pp/adj, which predicates
# nothing. Declaring it anyway would add a premise to every assert rule for no gain.
focus is a imperative
be is a imperative
run is a imperative
on is a preposition
cautious is a adj
decisive is a adj

iclause expands to imperative plus np
iclause expands to imperative plus pp
iclause expands to imperative plus adj
clause expands to iclause

slot imp in iclause from imperative plus np is left head
slot target in iclause from imperative plus np is right head
slot imp in iclause from imperative plus pp is left head
slot target in iclause from imperative plus pp is right pobj
slot imp in iclause from imperative plus adj is left head
slot target in iclause from imperative plus adj is right head

# `does` is a LITERAL in the predicate position (it names no slot), exactly as `is_a` is in the
# lines above -- the declaration surface already reads an unrecognized predicate as a literal word,
# so the command triple needs no new mechanism. The router reads (imperative-word, target).
iclause commands imp does target
